'''[[structural]] [[isomerism]]'''
#{{chemistry}} a form of isomerism in which the same [[atom]]s are [[arranged]] in [[different]] [[order]]s; either having the same or different [[functional group]]s
===Examples===
* same functional group
** n-butanol - CH<sub>3</sub>(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>3</sub>OH
** 2-methyl-propanol - (CH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>CHCH<sub>2</sub>OH
* different functional groups
** ethanol - CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OH
** di-metyhyl-ether - CH<sub>3</sub>OCH<sub>3</sub>
